These short formularies have been replaced in the Milanese use by the Unde et memoreS, etc„ continuing the Roman Canon. But even here also we can distinguish in the most ancient manuscripts a trace of conformity with the Gallican use. In these manuscripts the prayers Unde et memores, Supra quae, Supplices te reflamus, Memento, and Nobis quoque, are omitted on Maundy Thursday, and are replaced by the following formulary ¹ :—

Haec facimus, haec celebramus, tua, Domine, praecepta servantes et ad communionem inviolabilem hoo ipsum quod corpus Domini sumimus mortem dominicam nuntiamus.
